Create Databases required for the Project 6

These Steps will be performed in SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)

       1.  Right Click on Databases, then click on New Database.

       2. Name the Database. (ConsumerComplaints_Staging)

       3. Click Ok to create the Database, then refresh Database to locate New Database Created.



Repeat this step for all those 3 steps we are looking to create.

  • ConsumerComplaints_ODS
  • ConsumerComplaints_DW

Once you create the 3 databases we can move forward to the next step

  • ConsumerComplaints_Staging
  • ConsumerComplaints_ODS
  • ConsumerComplaints_DW


Data Source

The first question that needs to be addressed is "Where can we find the raw data that we can process?".

I located the data on the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) main website. 

URL http://files.consumerfinance.gov/ccdb/complaints.json.zip


Click the link to download the dataset for the project. The supplementary dataset (excel files) is provided in the project zip file SourceData file    

 The JSON is quite large 1.9GB, You have to  use an online splitter  (https://pinetools.com/split-files) to split the file to smaller sizes, after downloading and unzip the JSON file.





-         Choose the file path

-         Choose the number of files, to split the large file into

-         Click SPLIT FILE

-         Done, download individual file to a folder named SourceData



I have provided all the files, in the ConsumerComplaint Project.zip that will be needed to recreate this project. Take time to read the through the README file.
